  "summaries": [
    "The <b>Copper Axe</b> is the first <linked>axe</linked> the player will obtain, and is weaker than the <linked>Iron</linked> or <linked>Lead Axe</linked>. It has an alternate ore version, the <linked>Tin Axe</linked>, which is slightly stronger. Newly created characters will spawn with this item in their third inventory slot. Alternately, it can be purchased from the <linked>Merchant</linked> for <span class=\"coin\" title=\"4 Silver Coins\" data-sort-value=\"400\"><span class=\"sc\">4</span></span>. Like all axes, it is used to cut down <linked>trees</linked>, <linked>Cacti</linked>, <linked>Giant Glowing Mushrooms</linked>, and <span class=\"eil\"><span><linked>Fallen Logs</linked></span><span class=\"eico s i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i></span></span>.",
    "Its best <linked>modifier</linked> is <b>Light</b> for harvesting purposes and either <b>Agile</b> or <b>Forceful</b>/<b>Strong</b> for combat purposes, due to its unusually low base damage. Though it can obtain the <b>Ruthless</b> modifier, the reduced knockback may be undesirable for early stages of the game."
